ANC Chairperson, Gwede Mantashe comments. Courtesy of #DStv403 EASTERN CAPE - ANC Chairperson, Gwede Mantashe, says the party is not using the step-aside resolution to target individuals. He says the rule is not new, and leaders have adhered to it before. READ: Holomisa calls for Mkhize to step down Mantashe was speaking at the party's Sarah Baartman Region in the Eastern Cape. The governing party says members facing serious criminal offences must step aside.